org.orgName: District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington

body.p: UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON NORTHERN DIVISION
THE PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA, To HENRY M. WHITE, United States of Commissioner of Immigration,

WE COMMAND YOU, that you have the body of John Matthews by you imprisoned and detained, as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said John Matthews shall be called or charged, before the Honorable Jeremiah Neterer, United States District Judge for the Western District of Washington, at the court room of said court in the City of Seattle in the Northern Division of said District on the 29th day of September, A.D. 1921, at ten o'clock in the forenoon, to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning him, the said John Matthews And have you then and there this writ.

WITNESS the Honorable Jeremiah Neterer, Judge of the United States District Court for the Western District of Washington, this 19th day of September in the year of our Lord on thousand nine hundred and twenty-one.
FILED IN THE UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT Western District of Washington Northen Division
F.M. Harshberger, Clerk By S.E. Leitch Deputy
